A Magistratesâ€™ Court in Iyaganku, Ibadan on Friday ordered that a vagrant, Sunday John be remanded in a correctional centre for alleged murder. The police charged John, whose residential address was not provided with murder. The Magistrate, Mrs I. O Osho, did not take the plea of John for want in jurisdiction. She directed the police to return the case file to the Director of Public Prosecutions (DPP) for legal advice.   Four bandits killed, woman gunrunner held in Kaduna     Military hails rescue of two Chibok girls     Man kills three-year old, threatens dad in Anambra   She adjourned the case until Aug. 31, for mention. Earlier, the Prosecution Counsel, ASP Foluke Adedosu told the court that John committed the offence on June 7, at about 5 p.m, at Aba-Emo village, Ile-Ido, Omi-Adio area, Ibadan. She alleged that John caused the death of one Rabiu Salami, 30. She said the offence contravened the provisions of sections 316, 319 of the Criminal laws of Oyo State, 2000. (NAN)